snippet: After decades of fights, California’s chief coastal regulator approved a scaled-back development plan on Wednesday by a Clint Eastwood-backed group on a swath of real estate covered by rare Monterey pines.
abstract: California Coastal Commission approves a scaled-back plan by Clint Eastwood-backed developer Pebble Beach to build 90 homes in the Del Monte Forest of Monterey County.
lead_paragraph: After decades of fights, California’s chief coastal regulator approved a scaled-back development plan on Wednesday by a Clint Eastwood-backed group on a swath of real estate covered by rare Monterey pines.

headline.main: California: Compromise Ends Battle Over Development
headline.print_headline: California: Compromise Ends Battle Over Development Among Rare Pines
